    "department": "Marketing",
    "description": "ABOUT SOLACE\n\nHealthcare in the U.S. is fundamentally broken. The system is so complex that 88% of U.S. adults do not have the health literacy necessary to navigate it without help. Solace cuts through the red tape of healthcare by pairing patients with expert advocates and giving them the tools to make better decisions—and get better outcomes.\n\nWe're a Series C startup, founded in 2022 and backed by Inspired Capital, Craft Ventures, Torch Capital, Menlo Ventures, Signalfire, and IVP. Our U.S. based team is lean, mission-driven, and growing quickly.\n\nSolace isn't a place to coast. We're here to redefine healthcare—and that demands urgency, precision, and heart. If you're looking to stretch yourself, sharpen your edge, and do the best work of your life alongside a team that cares deeply, you're in the right place. We’re intense, and we like it that way.\n\nRead more in our Bloomberg funding announcement here https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2026-02-10/vcs-give-solace-health-1-billion-valuation-for-patient-advocacy-tech?accessToken=eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9.eyJzb3VyY2UiOiJTdWJzY3JpYmVyR2lmdGVkQXJ0aWNsZSIsImlhdCI6MTc3MDczMDg4MywiZXhwIjoxNzcxMzM1NjgzLCJhcnRpY2xlSWQiOiJUQThVUzhLR0NURzEwMCIsImJjb25uZWN0SWQiOiJBRDYxODI0MTc0ODM0MTk0QTRENUZFNzkwMzNGMDJGNSJ9.TE2pFUAOQAPMUXFlzoQ7zeJvctq7cSibbZqtIwhW-2U\u0026leadSource=uverify+wall.\n\n\nABOUT THE ROLE\n\nWe’re seeking a Junior SEO Specialist with 2–3 years of experience to help scale Solace’s organic growth across traditional search and emerging AI platforms.\n\nThis is not a blog-content role. You’ll work at the intersection of AI visibility, performance-driven content, authority building, and technical SEO. You’ll execute against a clear strategic roadmap while operating with autonomy and ownership.\n\nReporting into Growth leadership, you’ll collaborate closely with CRO, Product, and Engineering to ensure Solace is discoverable, trusted, and conversion-ready at scale.\n\nApplicants must be based in the United States.\n\n\nWHAT YOU’LL DO\n\nAdvance AI \u0026 Search Visibility\n\n - Execute initiatives that improve Solace’s visibility across Google and AI platforms (e.g., LLM-driven search experiences)\n\n - Optimize FAQ and entity signals to improve citation potential\n\n - Track AI and organic visibility trends and surface opportunities proactively\n\nDrive Performance SEO\n\n - Optimize high-intent pages tied directly to patient acquisition and revenue\n\n - Conduct keyword research focused on commercial and problem-aware queries\n\n - Support expansion of condition, insurance, and marketplace pages\n\n - Continuously refresh and improve existing content based on performance data\n\nSupport Authority \u0026 Backlink Growth\n\n - Identify high-value backlink opportunities and build outreach lists\n\n - Execute outreach campaigns and track placements\n\n - Assist in developing linkable assets and authoritative resource content\n\n - Monitor backlink health and referring domain growth\n\nMaintain Technical SEO Excellence\n\n - Conduct site audits using tools like Screaming Frog, Ahrefs and Google Search Console\n\n - Identify crawl, indexation, and internal linking opportunities\n\n - Document technical recommendations clearly for Engineering\n\n - QA implementations to ensure best-in-class execution\n\nOwn Performance Tracking\n\n - Monitor rankings, traffic, and conversion-related SEO metrics\n\n - Maintain dashboards and regular reporting\n\n - Translate data into actionable insights\n\n\nWHAT SUCCESS LOOKS LIKE\n\nA steady cadence of high-impact SEO initiatives that measurably increase organic visibility, authority, and patient acquisition — improving rankings across revenue-driving pages, expanding AI and search discoverability, strengthening our backlink profile, and building scalable systems that compound growth over time.\n\n\nWHAT YOU BRING TO THE TABLE\n\n - 2–3 years of hands-on SEO experience in-house or at an agency\n\n - Demonstrated experience improving rankings, traffic, or organic growth metrics\n\n - Familiarity with technical SEO fundamentals (crawlability, indexation, schema, internal linking)\n\n - Experience using tools such as Ahrefs, SEMrush, Screaming Frog, and Google Search Console\n\n - Exposure to backlink outreach or digital PR initiatives\n\n - Strong analytical skills and comfort working in spreadsheets\n\n - Clear written communication skills\n\n - High agency, strong ownership mindset, and bias toward execution\n\nNice to Have:\n\n - Experience in healthcare, marketplaces, or regulated industries\n\n - Exposure to AI-driven search trends or structured data strategy\n\n - Experience collaborating cross-functionally with Engineering or Product teams\n\nApplicants must be based in the United States.\n\nUp for the Challenge?\n\nWe look forward to meeting you.\n\nFraudulent Recruitment Advisory: Solace Health will NEVER request bank details or offer employment without an interview. All legitimate communications come from official solace.health emails only or ashbyhq.com http://ashbyhq.com. Report suspicious activity to recruiting@solace.health or advocate@solace.health.",
